winning_structure.name: UBX-TIM-TP
winning_structure.description: This message contains information on the timing of the next pulse at the TIMEPULSEO output. The recommended configuration when using this message is to set both the measurement rate (CFG-RATE) and the timepulse frequency (CFG-TP) to 1 Hz.

fields.name: towMS
fields.description: Time pulse time of week according to time base

fields.name: week
fields.description: Time pulse week number according to time base

structure.name: UBX-TIM-TP
structure.description: This message contains information on the timing of the next pulse at the time pulse output.

fields.name: towMS
fields.description: Time pulse time of week according to time base

fields.name: week
fields.description: Time pulse week number according to time base

bits.name: timeBase
bits.description: 0 = Time base is GNSS; 1 = Time base is UTC

bits.name: utc
bits.description: 0 = UTC not available; 1 = UTC available

bits.name: raim
bits.description: (T)RAIM information: 0 = Information not available; 1 = Not active; 2 = Active

bits.name: qErrInvalid
bits.description: 0 = Quantization error valid; 1 = Quantization error invalid

bits.name: TpNotLocked
bits.description: 0 = Next TP is locked to GNSS; 1 = Next TP is based on local time and not locked to GNSS - week/tow may be invalid

bits.name: timeRefGnss
bits.description: GNSS reference information. Only valid if time base is GNSS (timeBase=0). 0 = GPS; 1 = GLONASS; 2 = BeiDou; 3 = Galileo; 4 = NavIC; 15 = Unknown

bits.name: utcStandard
bits.description: UTC standard identifier. Only valid if time base is UTC (timeBase=1). 0 = Information not available; 1 = Communications Research Laboratory (CRL), Tokyo, Japan; 2 = National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST); 3 = U.S. Naval Observatory (USNO); 4 = International Bureau of Weights and Measures (BIPM); 5 = European laboratories

7 = National Time Service Center (NTSC), China
